HEADWORD: Thyro-
<hw>Thy"ro-</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A combining form used in anatomy to
indicate <xex>connection with</xex>, or <xex>relation to</xex>, <xex>the
thyroid body</xex> or <xex>the thyroid cartilage</xex>; <as>as,
<ex>thyro</ex>hyal</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thyroarytenoid</ent>⟦br⟧
